Instructions for the TA to make the working solution of resazurin:

Don gloves while working with resazurin!
When using DMSO (concentrated) work under the fume hood!
Once stock solution is made fume hood is no longer required. 

1. Make stock resazurin solution 

To make the resazurin stock solution (10 mL) mix the following in a falcon tube under a fume hood (DMSO volatile). 
We will use this solution for multiple trials. 

- 0.5 g resazurin salt (stored in upper chemical storage cabinets in storage room between FTR113 and FTR129)
- 10 mL DI water (white tap in FTR129, let run for a bit first)
- 10 µL DMSO (located in flammable storage cabinet under fume hood in FTR113)

Store in a dark fridge or freezer. 

2. Make working resazurin solution

The working solution requires the following: 

- Filtered seawater (DI water with Instant Ocean adjusted to 23-25 ppt or filtered (<1um) seawater) 
- Resazurin stock solution as made above in step 1 
- DMSO 
- Antibiotic solution 100x Penn/Strep & 100x Fungizone (stored in freezer in FTR129)
  - this should be kept frozen in a dark freezer and thawed before use 
  - thaw in the dark or cover with aluminum foil
  
For the FISH 460 Crab Lab, each crab will need ~35 mL of working solution to be submerged in the 'jello shot' plastic cups.
For each lab session, multiply the number of metabolic trials by 35mL to find the total working solution needed. 

For example, if each group has 12 *hemigrapsus* and 2 *carcinus* crabs (14 total),and there are 5 groups all running metabolic activity trials, 
we will need 14*5*35 = 2450 mL of working solution. We can round up to 3L of working solution per lab. 

You can mix 1L a a time in corning jars:
- 986.8 mL filtered seawater (DI water with Instant Ocean adjusted to 23-25 ppt or filtered <1μm seawater)
  - measure this out in a 1L graduted cylinder
  - or 500 + 487 mL in a 50mL graduated cylinder
- 2.2 mL resazurin stock solution (from step 1 above)
  - measure this out using a serological pipetter 
- 1 mL DMSO
  - measure this out using a P1000
- 10 mL antibiotic solution (100x Penn/Strep & 100x Fungizone)
  - meaure this out using a ~25mL serological pipetter

Or all at once...

3L of working solution can be made by mixing: 
- 2960 mL filtered seawater (DI water with Instant Ocean adjusted to 23-25 ppt or filtered <1μm seawater)
- 6.7 mL resazurin stock solution (from step 1 above)
- 3 mL DMSO
- 30 mL antibiotic solution (100x Penn/Strep & 100x Fungizone)